    "question": "<div><p>Design and implement a TwoSum class. It should support the following operations: <code>add</code> and <code>find</code>.</p>\n\n<p><code>add</code> - Add the number to an internal data structure.<br>\n<code>find</code> - Find if there exists any pair of numbers which sum is equal to the value.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>add(1); add(3); add(5);\nfind(4) -&gt; true\nfind(7) -&gt; false\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong>Example 2:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>add(3); add(1); add(2);\nfind(3) -&gt; true\nfind(6) -&gt; false</pre>\n</div>",
    "url": "https://leetcode.com/problems/two-sum-iii-data-structure-design/",
