    "title": "242. Valid Anagram",
    "question": "<div><p>Given two strings <em>s</em> and <em>t&nbsp;</em>, write a function to determine if <em>t</em> is an anagram of <em>s</em>.</p>\n\n<p><b>Example 1:</b></p>\n\n<pre><b>Input:</b> <em>s</em> = \"anagram\", <em>t</em> = \"nagaram\"\n<b>Output:</b> true\n</pre>\n\n<p><b>Example 2:</b></p>\n\n<pre><b>Input:</b> <em>s</em> = \"rat\", <em>t</em> = \"car\"\n<b>Output: </b>false\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><br>\nYou may assume the string contains only lowercase alphabets.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Follow up:</strong><br>\nWhat if the inputs contain unicode characters? How would you adapt your solution to such case?</p>\n</div>",
