    "diff": "Easy",
    "title": "429. N-ary Tree Level Order Traversal",
    "question": "<div><p>Given an n-ary tree, return the level order traversal of its nodes' values. (ie, from left to right, level by level).</p>\n\n<p>For example, given a <code>3-ary</code> tree:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2018/10/12/narytreeexample.png\" style=\"width: 100%; max-width: 300px;\"></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>We should return its level order traversal:</p>\n\n<pre>[\n     [1],\n     [3,2,4],\n     [5,6]\n]\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><b>Note:</b></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>The depth of the tree is at most <code>1000</code>.</li>\n\t<li>The total number of nodes is at most <code>5000</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>",
    "url": "https://leetcode.com/problems/n-ary-tree-level-order-traversal/",
