    "question": "<div class=\"sql-schema-wrapper__3VBi\"><a class=\"sql-schema-link__3cEg\">SQL Schema<svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"1em\" height=\"1em\" class=\"icon__3Su4\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M10 6L8.59 7.41 13.17 12l-4.58 4.59L10 18l6-6z\"></path></svg></a></div><div><p>Table:&nbsp;<code>Activity</code></p>\n\n<pre>+--------------+---------+ Column Name  | Type    |\n+--------------+---------+ player_id    | int     | device_id    | int     | event_date   | date    | games_played | int     |\n+--------------+---------+\n(player_id, event_date) is the primary key of this table.\nThis table shows the activity of players of some game.\nEach row is a record of a player who logged in and played a number of games (possibly 0) before logging out on some day using some device.\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Write a&nbsp;SQL query that reports&nbsp;the <strong>device</strong>&nbsp;that is first logged in&nbsp;for each player.</p>\n\n<p>The query result format is in the following example:</p>\n\n<pre>Activity table:\n+-----------+-----------+------------+--------------+ player_id | device_id | event_date | games_played |\n+-----------+-----------+------------+--------------+ 1         | 2         | 2016-03-01 | 5            | 1         | 2         | 2016-05-02 | 6            | 2         | 3         | 2017-06-25 | 1            | 3         | 1         | 2016-03-02 | 0            | 3         | 4         | 2018-07-03 | 5            |\n+-----------+-----------+------------+--------------+\n\nResult table:\n+-----------+-----------+ player_id | device_id |\n+-----------+-----------+ 1         | 2         | 2         | 3         | 3         | 1         |\n+-----------+-----------+</pre></div>",
