    "question": "<div><p>Given a sorted array consisting of only integers where every element appears exactly twice except for one element which appears exactly&nbsp;once. Find this single element that appears only once.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><b>Example 1:</b></p>\n\n<pre><b>Input:</b> [1,1,2,3,3,4,4,8,8]\n<b>Output:</b> 2\n</pre>\n\n<p><b>Example 2:</b></p>\n\n<pre><b>Input:</b> [3,3,7,7,10,11,11]\n<b>Output:</b> 10\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><b>Note:</b> Your solution should run in O(log n) time and O(1) space.</p>\n</div>",
